review_blob: At brewery. Murky cloudy. Smoke aroma is too strong. Taste is too smoky to be appealing. Cannot get past it. Very astringent in the palate. Not drinkable.
On tap at brewery. Medium lemon and light smoke aroma with light pomme esters. Flavor is lemon, wheat, with a light smoke taste. Light mouthfeel and lemony sour aftertaste. Awesome.
Jester King evaluations are purely hedonistic as beer styles are meaningless when using a farmhouse. Nice farmhouse twist to a stout but oats not present at all.
Fruity farmhouse aromas. Flavor is not balanced. Too fruity without balancing spice flavors. Too much sweetness for a saison.

Underwhelming aroma, very light fruit and sour notes, faint brett. Amber almost clear app. Flavors are very balanced with fruit notes of tangerine citrus and stone fruit. Brett and sour notes after mild. Too young now but will get better.
beer_name: Jester King / Side Project / Off Color Intersection of Species

review_blob: Very balanced mix of farmhouse and subtle smoke malt. Nothing like an Alt: sweeter, cloudy, wrong yeast character, wrong hop profile.
Nice farmhouse beer. Aroma is very inviting but there is a flavor and palate astringency that affects drinkability.
beer_name: Jester King Le Petit Prince Farmhouse Table Beer (Batch 11+)

review_blob: Smells more fruity, tropical than a pale ale. Cloudy like a weissbier. Tastes like a Shandy. I imagine a non beer drinker may enjoy this. It is a nice palate cleanser and it is fine with me but not even close to a pils. Not lager like at all.
Aroma has low herbal hops and low grainy pils malt. No esters, DMS or diacetyl. Taste of hops is low, malt is unidimensional pils flavor. A bit stale. Palate is s bit thin. Very drinkable pils
Tap at Draught House. Old hop moth ball aroma. Great appearance. Bitterness is a bit harsh but not spalt like. Lacks maltiness. Palate is a bit harsh. Messy overall. Not at all like an alt.

Aroma of earthy hops, caramel, toast. Amber clear color with tan head with good retention. Flavors of earthy hop bitterness, caramel, toast, butterscotch and diacetyl. ASTRINGENT palate. High residual bitterness.
Aroma is grassy with no noble hops. Flavor of astringent hops that mask the malt. Malt flavor is grainy, simple and clearly not decocted. Rather underwhelming.
Aromas of caramel, toast. Dark Brown with good head. Flavors of dark caramel, toast and sweet malt. Very balanced but simple.
beer_name: Big Boss Bad Penny Brown Ale

review_blob: Nice aroma of spicy hops and grading pils malt. Head retention not perfect. The spalter flavor is similar to the one of an alt beer, I would have liked something less harsh. Some malt body remains; nice! Spalter hops also provide a bit of palate astringency. Balanced finish with malt sweetness and hop residue that makes you drink. Worse than the best Urquell but probably the best pils in America.

On tap at Whip In, Austin. Smells of high-alpha noble hops with some background esters (high fermentation temp?). Good appearance, the foam did not last as in a perfect pils. The bitterness was harsh, unlike an aroma noble hop. Hop flavor was not smooth and got in the way of malt flavor. Palate was too astringent. Finish was harsh bitter (for a pils). Not a bad drinking experience. Tasted almost like a German IPA and if judged like that it would be a good beer, just not a great Pils.

Aroma similar to Dead Pony from Brew dog, very dank hops and not much else. Flavor of grassy, oniony hops and a tiny bit of sweet simple malt. Not balanced, too much vegetable hop flavor. Very grassy palate. Bitter hop aftertaste. I wonder where the Citra and Mosaic went... Not present here. This beer taste like Columbus and Chinook.

Spicy hop, noble like but not as smooth with a bit of pils bready malt aroma. Cloudy with nice head. Firm but astringent and grassy hop flavor. Malt flavor is simple. Noticeable palate astringency. Bitter finish and aftertaste.
Low American hop aroma. Too low a head. American hop flavor with tartness. OK but tastes gimmicky.
beer_name: Blue Owl Spirit Animal Sour Pale Ale

review_blob: A bit of with diaper vomit aromas and flavor. Malty and caramel flavor is also there but you cannot get past the off flavors.
beer_name: Blue Owl Van Dayum! Sour Red Ale

review_blob: Not as sour as a Berliner. A bit of wheat aroma and not much else. Color is golf with not a much foam as ac Berliner. Taste is tart but not sour as a Berliner. OK but not great.
beer_name: Blue Owl Little Boss Sour Session Wheat

review_blob: The helles that nobody likes in Munich. Oxidized aroma, weird metalic taste. Why would anyone drink this beer with other helles around.
A great helles. Low mittelfrueh and pilsner malt aroma. Good malt flavor, less rich than Augustiner. Great bitterness for a helles. Very well brewed helles.

Too clear, too dark (light amber), and not enough carbonation for a wit. There is a low coriander aroma combined with wheat aromas. There is a hint of citrus, not similar to bitter orange. The taste is a bit too bitter for a wit, but ok if not judged within the wit style. Too sharp for a wit. Not a bad beer but just a bad wit.

Nice malt and spice (spruce) aroma. Clear amber with low head that disappears immediately. Taste is malty simple, unidimensional with no complexity. Overly boozy for 6.4%. Tastes like an italian doppio malto beer, boozy and thin. I will skip in the future.

Bottle from Costco. Clear light amber with neat head that goes down at a normal rate. Med low aroma of citrus and tropical fruit hops with a low malt aroma. Taste also of malt and tropical fruit hops. Bitterness is too low, making the beer seem watery. Thin palate with no other sensations. Dry finish with no significant aftertaste.

I am rating this as an Alt Bier per the bottle and Rate Beer. The aroma has more English caramel notes and less hops than a normal Alt. The hop aroma is not far but not quite the one of an Alt. The bitterness level is lower than an Alt and it has a caramelly sweet mid palate that is not appropriate for an Alt.
The finish is not as dry or as hoppy as an Alt. 
Ok beer but not close to a Dusseldorf Alt.
UPDATED: MAR 21, 2016

Cloudy Amber, not clear. Chill haze? Head dissipates quickly. Excellent earthy aroma with malt background. Perfect earthy bitterness and hop flavor with malty, toasty breast flavors. Dry finish with English hop residue. Great beer.

Minor Saaz and Czech diacetyl aroma. Flavor is malt and diacetyl with minor hop flavor 
Dry finish.
Bottled Amber beer with off white head. Alcohol was the most predominant note in both aroma and flavor. Unpleasant malt liquor-like drink. Does baladin have a good beer?
Smoke and sour notes in the aroma. A bit rough and astringent with too much smoke. Dry finish.
Classic saison fresh aroma. Flavor is rough but still pleasant. Needs more hop bitterness and less astringency. Dry finish with grassy aftertaste.
beer_name: Birrificio La Casa Di Cura T.A.C.

review_blob: American hop aroma. Pleasant flavor with toasty malt and citrus hops. Dry finish. Nice.
American hop aroma. Bitterness is too grassy and gets in the way of balance. Dry finish with Grassy aftertaste.
Disappointing aroma with just a bit of toast. A sour note in the flavor predominates with toast roast and chocolate in the background. Not only sour but too roasty for a porter.
Caramel and sweet spice aromas. Caramel and sweet alcohol flavor. Needs bitterness. Semi sweet finish.
Peppery yeast aromas. Pilsner malt and spicy great flavor with balanced bitterness. Dry finish.
Clear Amber. Munich aroma with hoppy undertones. Malty caramel and noble hop flavor. Firm bitterness Dry finish
Funky Brett sour and fruit aroma. Great sweet and sour balance with Bert notes. Dry finish
Onion and Tropical fruit aroma. Grasy bitter flavor with rye and malt in a support role. Dry finish with Resiny aftertaste.
barely a hint of hop aroma. Oxidized sour flavor with little bitterness. Sour aftertaste.
Aggressive Oniony hop aroma. Astringent hop flavor hiding the malt. Astringent palate. Dry finish. Very grassy aftertaste.
Caramelly plum and date aroma with Christmas spice. Complex flavor of dried fruits mostly plum and spice with firm bitterness in the end. Dry finish. Extraordinary.
Faint hallertau aroma. Flavor of hops but malt hidden by high astringency. Dry astringent flavor.
Nice Munich malt aroma. Munich malt flavor with a hint of German hops. Low bitterness. semi sweet finish.
Classic Hallertau aroma with pils malt. Pils malt and go flavor. Very clean. Dry finish
Cloudy Amber with ale esters. Muddy taste with esters and make. Not hoppy. Dry finish.
Saaz and make aroma. Malty and Saaz flavor with firm bitterness. Dry hoppy finish. Great beer.
Clove and wheat Aroma. Wheat and clove in flavor as well. Effervescent. No astringency. Dry finish.

Caramelly Saaz aromas. Simple malt and caramel taste with good Saaz flavor and firm bitterness. 
Nice palate and dry hoppy finish that invites further drinking.
